template <int N>
struct Factorial {
  enum { value = N * Factorial<N - 1>::value };
};

template <>
struct Factorial<0> {
  enum { value = 1 };
};

int main() {
  std::cout << "The factorial of 5 is " << Factorial<5>::value << std::endl;
  return 0;
}

This program uses a technique called template metaprogramming, which allows you to perform computations at compile time. The Factorial template defines a recursive structure that calculates the factorial of N by multiplying N by the factorial of N - 1. The specialization of Factorial for N = 0 provides the base case, which returns a value of 1.

